s',2,'Heart','Given that one cardiac cycle takes 0.8 seconds and consists of atrial systole, ventricular systole, and joint diastole, what does the existence of joint diastole suggest about the heart''s workload?','The heart works continuously without any rest phase','The heart has a built-in recovery phase (joint diastole) in every cycle, allowing the chambers to refill and rest before the next contraction','The heart only contracts during ventricular systole and rests for the rest of the cycle','Joint diastole represents a failure of the SA node','B',5,0,0,5),(82,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'2','Digestion and Transport of Nutrients',2,'Heart','A student checks their pulse rate at rest and after exercise and finds it is significantly higher after exercise. Based on the chapter, which explanation is correct?','After exercise, blood pressure drops, causing the pulse to increase','After exercise, more energy is needed, so the heart rate increases to pump more blood; since pulse rate equals heart rate, the pulse also increases','After exercise, the SA node stops functioning, causing an irregular pulse','Pulse rate is independent of heart rate and increases due to body temperature alone','B',5,0,0,5),(83,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'2','Digestion and Transport of Nutrients',2,'Health of Heart','Deposition of fat in arterial walls causes a condition called:','Hypertension','Atherosclerosis','Coronary thrombosis','Hypotension','B',1,0,0,1),(84,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'2','Digestion and Transport of Nutrients',2,'Health of Heart','A stroke is caused by:','Blood clotting in the coronary artery','Blockage or rupture of blood vessels in the brain','Deposition of fat only in peripheral vessels','Excessive exercise causing heart overload','B',1,0,0,1),(85,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'2','Digestion and Transport of Nutrients',2,'Health of Heart','Which of the following is listed as a factor that adversely affects the health of the 