ecule moves from higher to lower concentration using a channel protein but no energy. A second molecule moves from lower to higher concentration using a carrier protein and energy. Which processes are these, respectively?','Active transport; facilitated diffusion','Facilitated diffusion (channel protein); active transport','Osmosis; diffusion','Diffusion; osmosis','B',5,0,0,5),(260,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'1','To Life Processes',1,'Plasma Membrane and Exchange of Substances','A root cell absorbs mineral ions from soil even though the ion concentration in the soil is lower than inside the cell. Which process explains this, and what does the cell require for it?','Osmosis; a semi-permeable membrane and a concentration gradient','Simple diffusion; no energy or proteins','Active transport; energy and carrier proteins in the plasma membrane','Facilitated diffusion; channel proteins without energy','C',5,0,0,5),(261,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'1','To Life Processes',1,'Plasma Membrane and Exchange of Substances','The chapter states that water moves through osmosis and oxygen moves through diffusion. What is the one structural feature of the plasma membrane that makes both possible?','Its rigid cell-wall-like structure','Its selectively permeable nature — allowing small molecules like water and oxygen to pass while controlling the entry of ions and larger molecules','Its ability to produce energy for all transport processes','Its ability to synthesise carrier proteins on demand','B',5,0,0,5),(262,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'1','To Life Processes',1,'Plasma Membrane and Exchange of Substances','Compare active transport and facilitated diffusion. A cell undergoing active transport would have what, that a cell doing facilitated diffusion would NOT require?','Semi-permeable membrane','Concentration gradient','Membrane proteins','Energy (ATP)','D',5,0,0,5),(263,'Kerala',9,'English','Biology','MCQ',1,'1','To Life Processes',1,'Photosynthesi