d for nearly one century because it could:','Explain the presence of electrons','Account for isotopes','Describe nuclear structure','Logically explain the formation of substances','D',3,0,0,3),(608,'Kerala',9,'English','Chemistry','MCQ',1,'1','Structure of Atom',4,'Dalton''s Atomic Theory','According to Dalton, atoms cannot be divided during chemical reactions. Which later discovery directly contradicted this?','Classification of elements into metals and non-metals','Discovery of subatomic particles like the electron','Formation of compounds in simple ratios','Isolation of elements by electrolysis','B',3,0,0,3),(609,'Kerala',9,'English','Chemistry','MCQ',1,'1','Structure of Atom',4,'Dalton''s Atomic Theory','A rubbed comb attracting bits of paper suggests:','All matter is made of molecules','Atoms cannot be created or destroyed','Electric charges are present within substances','Compounds form in simple ratios','C',4,0,0,4),(610,'Kerala',9,'English','Chemistry','MCQ',1,'1','Structure of Atom',4,'Dalton''s Atomic Theory','Which postulate of Dalton was disproved by the discovery of isotopes?','Atoms cannot be created or destroyed','Compounds form by simple ratios','Atoms of the same element are identical in mass','Atoms cannot be divided during chemical reactions','C',4,0,0,4),(611,'Kerala',9,'English','Chemistry','MCQ',1,'1','Structure of Atom',4,'Dalton''s Atomic Theory','Which of the following is NOT a postulate of Dalton''s atomic theory?','Matter is made up of atoms','Atoms can neither be created nor destroyed','Atoms of the same element are identical in mass','Atoms are made up of electrons, protons and neutrons','D',5,0,0,5),(612,'Kerala',9,'English','Chemistry','MCQ',1,'1','Structure of Atom',4,'Dalton''s Atomic Theory','Dalton proposed that atoms of different elements differ in properties and mass. Which later discovery showed that the difference in mass between elements arises from their nuclear composition?','Faraday''s law of electrolysis','Chadwick''s disc