 They cut transversal CD: first segment = 6. Find the second segment of CD:','6','12','9','8','B',3,0,0,3),(1525,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Parallel lines cut two transversals. First transversal: 3 cm, 7 cm. Second transversal: x cm, 14 cm. Find x:','14','7','6','21','C',3,0,0,3),(1526,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Three parallel lines divide transversal l in the ratio 2:5. They divide transversal m into total length 21 cm. What are the two segments of m?','6 and 15','7 and 14','5 and 16','3 and 18','A',3,0,0,3),(1527,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Three parallel lines cut transversal AB such that AP:PB = 3:2 (P is the intersection point on AB between second and third lines). On transversal CD, if CQ = 9, find QD:','9','6','15','3','B',3,0,0,3),(1528,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Four parallel lines create three segments on transversal l: 2, 4, 6. Find the three segments on transversal m if the first segment of m is 3:','3, 6, 9','3, 4, 6','2, 4, 6','3, 3, 3','A',4,0,0,4),(1529,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Three parallel lines cut transversal AB in ratio 3:7. The total length of AB between outermost parallel lines is 40 cm. The length of each segment is:','12 and 28','20 and 20','10 and 30','15 and 25','A',4,0,0,4),(1530,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Three parallel lines divide two transversals proportionally. On transversal 1: segments are 5 and 15. On transversal 2: total length is 12. Find each segment of transversal 2:','6 and 6','3 and 9','4 and 8','2 and 10','B',4,0,0,4),(1531,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','A set of parallel lines divides one transversal in ratio a:b. The same lines divide a second transversal. If the second transversal''s total cut length is T, the first segment is:','T × b/(a+b)','T × a/(a+b)','T × (a+b)/a','T / (a+b)','B',4,0,0,4),(1532,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','The theorem on unequal division by parallel lines is a generalisation of which simpler result from this chapter?','The midpoint theorem','The equal division by equally spaced parallel lines','The triangle area formula','The Euler line property','B',5,0,0,5),(1533,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Parallel lines l₁, l₂, l₃ cut transversal AB in ratio AP:PB = m:n. They cut transversal CD in ratio CQ:QD. The theorem guarantees:','CQ:QD = n:m','CQ:QD = m:n regardless of the transversal''s direction or length','CQ = AP always','CQ:QD = m²:n²','B',5,0,0,5),(1534,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','Three parallel lines cut transversals l and m. On l: first segment = a, second = b. On m: first segment = c, second = d. The proportionality relation is:','a/b = d/c','a/b = c/d','a × d = b × c (same as a/b = c/d)','Both B and C','D',5,0,0,5),(1535,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Unequal Division','If three parallel lines divide transversal l in ratio 2:3 and transversal m in ratio 2:3, and a third transversal n is also cut by the same three parallel lines, what ratio will n be divided in?','3:02','4:09','2:03','It depends on n''s angle','C',5,0,0,5),(1536,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Triangle Division','A line drawn parallel to one side of a triangle divides the other two sides in:','Equal parts always','The same ratio','Inverse ratio','Ratio 1:2','B',1,0,0,1),(1537,'Kerala',9,'English','Maths','MCQ',1,'3','Parallel Lines',13,'Triangle Division','In triangle ABC, a line parallel to BC meets AB at D and AC at E. Then AD/DB equals:','BC/DE','AE/EC','AB/AC','DE/BC','B',1,0,0,1),(1538,'Kerala',9,'Engl