s in Mesolithic cave art suggest?','Mesolithic humans had no concerns about survival','There was some leisure time beyond basic survival needs','Mesolithic humans were more advanced than Neolithic ones','Amusements were religious rituals only','B',5,0,0,5),(2149,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Mesolithic Age','Which Mesolithic characteristic suggests that the transition toward a more settled lifestyle had begun?','Use of microliths','Cave paintings','Indications of domestication of animals','Hunting and gathering as livelihoods','C',5,0,0,5),(2150,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Mesolithic Age','Evidence at Sarai Nahar Rai shows that seeds were collected and stored. Why is this significant for understanding the transition from Mesolithic to Neolithic?','It shows agriculture had fully developed','It suggests the beginning of food storage, a precursor to agriculture','It proves Sarai Nahar Rai is a Neolithic site','It shows that rice was the first crop cultivated','B',5,0,0,5),(2151,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','What does the word ''Neolithic'' mean?','Old Stone','Middle Stone','New Stone','Metal Stone','C',1,0,0,1),(2152,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Who wrote the book ''Man Makes Himself'' which refers to important changes in the Neolithic Age?','Jawaharlal Nehru','Gordon Childe','Robert J. Braidwood','A.L. Basham','B',1,0,0,1),(2153,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','What is the ''Fertile Crescent''?','The region in Egypt where the Nile forms a crescent shape','The crescent-shaped region where agriculture is believed to have begun','A Neolithic tool shaped like a crescent','A region of South Asia associated with rice cultivation','B',1,0,0,1),(2154,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','The Neolithic site of Mehrgarh is now located in which country?','India','Iran','Pakistan','Iraq','C',1,0,0,1),(2155,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Which of the following is a Neolithic site in present-day Iraq?','Jericho','Ali Kosh','Jarmo','Mehrgarh','C',1,0,0,1),(2156,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','What was the first revolution mentioned in ''Man Makes Himself'' that transformed human economy in the Neolithic Age?','Using metals for tools','Man getting control over his own food supply through planting and domestication','Building permanent stone houses','Developing a writing system','B',2,0,0,2),(2157,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','What were Neolithic tools characterised by compared to earlier stone tools?','They were smaller (microliths)','They were polished','They were made of copper','They were rougher and heavier','B',2,0,0,2),(2158,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Which development in the Neolithic Age made the storage of grains possible?','Building of fortified cities','Introduction of pottery and use of bricks made of clay','Discovery of iron smelting','Domestication of horses','B',2,0,0,2),(2159,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Which crops were cultivated by the people of Jarmo in Iraq?','Rice and cotton','Barley and two varieties of wheat','Millet and sorghum','Maize and sugarcane','B',2,0,0,2),(2160,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','The term ''Neolithic Revolution'' was coined by Gordon Childe to refer to what major change?','The discovery of fire','The transition from hunting-gathering to agriculture and animal domestication','The first use of stone tools','The development of writing','B',2,0,0,2),(2161,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Which of the following factors led humans to begin agriculture during the Neolithic Age?','Discovery of new hunting weapons','Population growth and shortage of food products','Floods that destroyed forests','Orders from rulers','B',3,0,0,3),(2162,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','What was the consequence of surplus agricultural production in the Neolithic Age?','More humans became hunters','A section of society was freed for other occupations like pottery and weaving','Humans returned to nomadic life','Trade with foreign countries began immediately','B',3,0,0,3),(2163,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','The Mehrgarh site is called ''the bread basket of Baluchistan''. What does this suggest about the region?','It was a region where metal tools were first used','It was an important early site of agriculture and animal domestication','It was the first site of urban civilisation','It was where the first humans lived','B',3,0,0,3),(2164,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Ali Kosh is a Neolithic site located in which present-day country?','Iraq','Pakistan','Iran','Turkey','C',3,0,0,3),(2165,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Why did the Neolithic humans transition from nomadic to settled life?','They were afraid of wild animals','Agriculture and animal domestication ensured steady food supply and led to permanent settlements','They were forced to by rulers','They discovered pottery which was too heavy to carry','B',3,0,0,3),(2166,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','The people of Jarmo made clay figures of animals and humans. The most prominent figure was that of a pregnant woman. What does this most likely suggest?','Women ruled Jarmo society','Beliefs or rituals related to fertility','Women were potters in Jarmo','Jarmo people worshipped all animals','B',4,0,0,4),(2167,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','How did agricultural surplus production lead to the formation of different occupational groups in Neolithic society?','Surplus forced all people to become farmers','Surplus freed some people from farming, allowing them to pursue pottery, weaving and other crafts','Surplus was traded, creating a merchant class only','Surplus caused population decline leading to specialisation','B',4,0,0,4),(2168,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Who led the archaeological excavations at Jarmo in the Kurdish Hills of Iraq?','Gordon Childe','A.L. Basham','Robert J. Braidwood','Jawaharlal Nehru','C',4,0,0,4),(2169,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Why does Gordon Childe call the changes of the Neolithic period a ''revolution''?','Because it involved violent conflict','Because it brought radical changes to human economy and social formation','Because it happened very quickly in one generation','Because it was led by a political leader','B',4,0,0,4),(2170,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','What distinguishes a Neolithic settlement from a Palaeolithic settlement?','Neolithic settlements used fire','Neolithic settlements were permanent agrarian villages with stored food and varied occupations','Neolithic settlements were entirely underground','Neolithic settlements had written laws','B',5,0,0,5),(2171,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','How did Neolithic tools help in the expansion of agriculture?','They helped humans fight enemies','They helped in tilling the soil and cutting down trees to create farmland','They were used to dig wells for irrigation','They were used to build grain storage structures','B',5,0,0,5),(2172,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','What connects the domestication of animals to the beginning of agriculture in the Neolithic Age?','Both required the development of metals','Both gave humans control over their food supply, transforming them from food-gatherers to food-producers','Both required permanent cities with stone walls','Both were caused by population decline','B',5,0,0,5),(2173,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','''Complex social organisation'' is listed as both a cause and an effect of Neolithic agriculture. Why might this be?','Complex society caused farming and farming in turn created more complex society through surplus and specialisation','Complex society was only a cause, not an effect','Farming always preceded social complexity in every society','Social organisation had no relationship with agriculture','A',5,0,0,5),(2174,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Jericho is a Neolithic site. In which present-day territory is it located?','Iraq','Iran','Jordan','Palestine/West Bank region','D',5,0,0,5),(2175,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Neolithic Age','Which statement best describes the significance of ''Man Makes Himself'' by Gordon Childe for studying the Neolithic Age?','It is the oldest known written text from the Neolithic period','It identifies two key revolutions — Neolithic and Urban — that transformed human civilization','It provides a list of all Neolithic archaeological sites worldwide','It argues that the Neolithic Age was less important than the Palaeolithic','B',5,0,0,5),(2176,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','Which was the first metal used by humans?','Iron','Bronze','Copper','Silver','C',1,0,0,1),(2177,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What is Bronze?','An alloy of iron and carbon','An alloy of copper and tin','Pure copper shaped into tools','An alloy of copper and zinc','B',1,0,0,1),(2178,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','The Harappan civilization belongs to which age?','Palaeolithic Age','Neolithic Age','Iron Age','Bronze Age','D',1,0,0,1),(2179,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','''Veda'' means which of the following?','Religion','Knowledge','Sacrifice','Ritual','B',1,0,0,1),(2180,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','The Vedic Age falls between which years BCE?','3000 BCE and 1500 BCE','1500 BCE and 600 BCE','600 BCE and 300 BCE','2500 BCE and 1000 BCE','B',1,0,0,1),(2181,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What is the Chalcolithic Age?','The age when only copper tools were used','The age when both copper tools and stone tools were used together','The age when only stone tools were used','The age when iron replaced stone','B',2,0,0,2),(2182,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What is the Sapta Sindhu region?','The seven sacred mountains of the Aryans','The region including the Indus River and its tributaries','The seven cities of the Harappan civilization','The area around the Ganga plain','B',2,0,0,2),(2183,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','Where did the Aryans who entered the Sapta Sindhu region originate from?','South India','Central Asia','Southeast Asia','The Mediterranean region','B',2,0,0,2),(2184,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What is the earliest of the four Vedas?','Yajurveda','Samaveda','Atharvaveda','Rigveda','D',2,0,0,2),(2185,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What is ''urbanisation'' as defined in the chapter?','Building of temples and palaces','When a densely populated region has majority earning through non-agrarian activities such as crafts and trade','The process of creating a written language','When a king conquers many territories','B',2,0,0,2),(2186,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','In the Vedic society, what was the role of Vaishyas?','Priestly rites','Governing and guarding the kingdom','Agriculture and trade','Serving the other three varnas','C',3,0,0,3),(2187,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','In which Indian states are many remains of the Chalcolithic Age found?','Punjab, Haryana and Rajasthan','Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh and Maharashtra','Gujarat, Bihar and Uttar Pradesh','Tamil Nadu, Karnataka and Andhra Pradesh','B',3,0,0,3),(2188,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What does the Harappan civilization''s Great Bath, well-planned streets, and granaries indicate?','Military power of the Harappans','Early urbanisation in Indian history','Religious practices of the Harappans','Agricultural techniques','B',3,0,0,3),(2189,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','The Vedic period is divided into Early and Later Vedic periods. What text was composed in the Early Vedic Period?','Yajurveda','Atharvaveda','Samaveda','Rigveda','D',3,0,0,3),(2190,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What developments in the Bronze Age (6000–3000 BCE) enabled the expansion of agriculture?','Use of copper tools replaced stone tools completely','Harnessing of oxen and winds, use of plough, wheelcart and boats, and advancement in metallurgy','Discovery of iron which replaced bronze','Decline of trade which forced people to farm','B',3,0,0,3),(2191,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','How did the Later Vedic period differ from the Early Vedic period in terms of women''s status?','Women''s social status improved in the Later Vedic period','Women''s social status declined in the Later Vedic period','Women''s status remained the same in both periods','Women had equal rights in both periods','B',4,0,0,4),(2192,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','Why is the Harappan civilization called the ''first urbanisation'' in Indian history?','It was India''s first kingdom','It shows the first evidence of organized urban life with planned cities, drainage and granaries in India','It was the first civilization to use metals in India','It was the first to practice agriculture in India','B',4,0,0,4),(2193,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','The language of the Aryans belonged to the Indo-European family. Which of the following is NOT listed as an Indo-European language?','Sanskrit','Greek','Tamil','Russian','C',4,0,0,4),(2194,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','How did the use of copper in early agrarian villages like Catal Huyuk and Ali Kosh lead to the Metal Age?','Copper was used to make pottery','Humans learned to turn raw copper into weapons and tools, marking the beginning of the Metal Age','Copper was used as a currency in these villages','Copper tools were weaker than stone tools, forcing improvements','B',4,0,0,4),(2195,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','What are the Brahmanas, Aranyakas and Upanishads in relation to Vedic literature?','They are the four Vedas','They are part of Vedic literature in addition to the four Vedas','They are post-Vedic works unrelated to Vedic literature','They are ancient historical records of Vedic wars','B',4,0,0,4),(2196,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','Which statement correctly contrasts copper tools with stone tools?','Stone tools can be reshaped more easily than copper tools','Copper tools are more durable and can be changed into suitable shapes unlike stone','Stone tools were sharper than copper tools','Copper tools were cheaper and easier to produce in the ancient period','B',5,0,0,5),(2197,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','The Yajnas (sacrifices) in the Early Vedic period were simple and could be performed by the head of the family. In the Later Vedic period they became complicated and expensive, becoming the privilege of a particular section. What does this change reveal about Later Vedic society?','Later Vedic society was more equal','Social hierarchy deepened and priestly privilege increased in Later Vedic society','Later Vedic society abandoned religious practices','The head of the family gained more power in Later Vedic period','B',5,0,0,5),(2198,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','After the decline of the Harappan civilization, the Aryans entered the Sapta Sindhu region. What does this suggest about the relationship between the Bronze Age Harappans and the later Vedic culture?','Aryans were the same as Harappans','There was a historical sequence: Harappan Bronze Age civilization declined, then Aryans brought Vedic culture','Harappan civilization and Vedic civilization existed simultaneously in the same region','The Vedic Age preceded the Bronze Age in India','B',5,0,0,5),(2199,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','The Varna system became stronger in the Later Vedic period. Which group served all three upper varnas?','Vaishyas','Kshatriyas','Sudras','Brahmins','C',5,0,0,5),(2200,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'1','Moving Forward from the Stone Age',22,'Metal Age','Why did the presence of copper at sites like Catal Huyuk (Turkey) and Ali Kosh (Iran) mark a turning point in human history?','These sites prove that metal use began in Asia only','It signalled the transition from stone tools to metal tools, enabling more durable and versatile implements','Copper was immediately replaced by iron at these sites','These are the only sites where copper was ever found in the ancient world','B',5,0,0,5);
