States',23,'Ideological Revolution in the Ganga Basin','What role did Vaishyas play in supporting new ideas of the 6th century BCE?','They funded military conquests','They had advanced materially through trade and desired higher social status','They composed new philosophical texts','They established the Mahajanapadas','B',3,0,0,3),(2207,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Ideological Revolution in the Ganga Basin','Which philosophical traditions emerged from the 6th century BCE intellectual revolution?','Vedanta and Yoga','Jain and Buddhist philosophies','Samkhya and Nyaya','Mimamsa and Vaisheshika','B',4,0,0,4),(2208,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Ideological Revolution in the Ganga Basin','Why was the 6th century BCE described as a remarkable period in world history?','Major empires were built across the world','New ideas spread simultaneously in India Iran China and Greece with political changes','Writing was invented in this period','The Iron Age began globally','B',4,0,0,4),(2209,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Ideological Revolution in the Ganga Basin','How did an agricultural economy based on cattle lead to opposition to Vedic practices?','Vedic practices promoted cattle ownership clashing with farmers','Vedic rituals required large-scale cattle sacrifice harming agricultural productivity','Agricultural wealth made Vedic priests jealous','Farmers could not afford priestly fees','B',5,0,0,5),(2210,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Ideological Revolution in the Ganga Basin','The 6th century BCE saw thinkers like Saratushtra in Iran and Confucius in China. What does this global pattern suggest?','These thinkers copied ideas from each other','Similar material conditions in different parts of the world simultaneously produced new intellectual movements','India was the only source of new philosophical thought','All these thinkers met at a single conference','B',5,0,0,5),(2211,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','Where was Vardhamana Mahavira born?','Kapilavastu Nepal','Kundagrama near Vaishali in Bihar','Pava near Patna','Bodh Gaya in Bihar','B',1,0,0,1),(2212,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','Who is the 24th Tirthankara in Jainism?','Rishabhadeva','Parswanatha','Vardhamana Mahavira','Ajita Kesakambalin','C',1,0,0,1),(2213,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','What does the term Tirthankara mean?','One who attained wisdom through asceticism','One who founded a new religion','One who conquered enemies','One who preached in Sanskrit','A',1,0,0,1),(2214,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','What are the Triratnas in Jainism?','The three Vedas','Right Belief Right Knowledge and Right Action','Non-violence Non-stealing and Non-lying','The three classes of monks','B',2,0,0,2),(2215,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','In which language did Mahavira share his ideas with the people?','Sanskrit','Pali','Prakrit','Tamil','C',2,0,0,2),(2216,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','Where did Mahavira attain Nirvana?','Vaishali','Bodh Gaya','Pava near Patna','Sarnath','C',2,0,0,2),(2217,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','Which of the following is a Jain doctrine as stated in the chapter?','Desire is the cause of sorrow','In this world everything has life and one must not harm any living being','The Middle Path avoids both extremes','There is no afterlife','B',3,0,0,3),(2218,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Jainism','How many Tirthankaras are there in Jainism?','12','18','24','32','C',3,0,0,3),(2219,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 