icant urbanisation','Kushinara was a Jain centre','Ananda was wrong about the development of cities','B',5,0,0,5),(2265,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Mahajanapadas or the Early States','How did the concept of ones own land arise as a result of the inextricable relationship with agriculture in the Janapada period?','Kings distributed land certificates to every farmer','Permanent agricultural settlement created emotional and political bonds to a specific territory leading to the idea of a homeland and state formation','The Vedas commanded people to stay in one place','Traders needed fixed addresses for commerce','B',5,0,0,5),(2266,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Rise of Magadha and Maurya Kingdom','Who founded the Maurya Kingdom?','Bimbisara','Asoka','Chandragupta Maurya','Sishunaga','C',1,0,0,1),(2267,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Rise of Magadha and Maurya Kingdom','What is Arthashastra and who wrote it?','A Buddhist text written by Asoka','An important historical document about the Maurya kingdom written by Kautilya','A Jain philosophical text by Mahavira','A collection of Vedic hymns','B',1,0,0,1),(2268,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Rise of Magadha and Maurya Kingdom','What is Asoka Dhamma?','Asoka''s tax collection system','The ideas propagated by Emperor Asoka to maintain peace and coexistence among his subjects','A military strategy of Emperor Asoka','A Buddhist scripture compiled by Asoka','B',1,0,0,1),(2269,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Rise of Magadha and Maurya Kingdom','In which year did Chandragupta Maurya defeat Dhanananda the last Nanda ruler?','321 BCE','261 BCE','273 BCE','300 BCE','A',1,0,0,1),(2270,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 1','MCQ',1,'2','Ideas and Early States',23,'Rise of Magadha and Maurya Kingdom','What were Punch Marked Coins made 