cture','What is the average height of the Himadri (Greater Himalayas)?','3500 m','4500 m','5000 m','6100 m','D',1,0,0,1),(2609,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'The Himalayas - Structure','The Himalayas consist of how many parallel ranges?','Two','Three','Four','Five','B',1,0,0,1),(2610,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'The Himalayas - Structure','Which Himalayan range is always snow-clad?','Shiwaliks','Himachal','Himadri','Trans Himalayas','C',1,0,0,1),(2611,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'Origin of the Himalayas','The Himalayas are which type of mountains?','Block mountains','Volcanic mountains','Fold mountains','Residual mountains','C',1,0,0,1),(2612,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'Origin of the Himalayas','What was the name of the ancient sea between the Indian Plate and the Eurasian Plate before the Himalayas formed?','Arabian Sea','Tethys Sea','Red Sea','Caspian Sea','B',1,0,0,1),(2613,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'Kashmir Himalaya','What is the height of K2 (Godwin Austin)?','8848 m','8611 m','8586 m','7756 m','B',1,0,0,1),(2614,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'Kashmir Himalaya','Dal Lake is located in which city?','Manali','Shimla','Srinagar','Leh','C',1,0,0,1),(2615,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'Himachal Himalaya','Which pass connects Kulu to the Lahul and Spiti valleys?','Baralacha La','Rohtang Pass','Banihal Pass','Bomdila Pass','B',1,0,0,1),(2616,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'Uttarakhand Himalaya','Which glacier is the origin of the river Ganga?','Siachen Glacier','Yamunotri Glacier','Gangotri Glacier','Boltoro Glacier','C',1,0,0,1),(2617,'Kerala',9,'English','Social 2','MCQ',1,'1','On the Roof of the World',27,'Cen